					<h3 class="text-danger" style="margin-top: -10px">Devil's Advocate</h3>
					<!-- article content -->
					<article>
						<div class="blog_post" style="margin-top: -10px">
							<span class="text-danger">
								Money starts to add up every month, $25 * 12 months = $300 / year for Android or IOS.
								<br/>
								If you purchase Android/IOS Indie license that is $50 * 12 months = $600 / year for Android and IOS.
								<br />
								But if I use Android Studio and its $Free.99!
							</span>
						</div>
						<div class="blog_post">
							<span class="text-info">
								It does come with a price but if your goal is to share code developing for multiple platforms its worth the price. I did not like the fact that I had to learn how to use Xamarin Studio but it was not bad at all, I actually prefer using Xamarin Studio now as Visual Studio has spoiled us .Net developers.  One thing to note is that Visual Studio users should have no problem at all navigating the options in Xamarin Studio and using the Nuget package manager.
							</span>
